{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/dsa/missing-number/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"df4cfd8c-c898-51db-b351-c0dd1ec609db","html":"<!-- Problem Statement -->\n<p>Given an array containing <em>n</em> distinct integers in the range [0, n], one number is\nmissing from the array. Find the missing number.</p>\n<p><em>Example 1</em><br>\n<strong>Input</strong>: [0, 2, 3]<br>\n<strong>Output</strong>: 1<br>\n<strong>Explanation</strong>: 1 is missing from the array.</p>\n<p><em>Example 2</em><br>\n<strong>Input</strong>: [0, 2, 1]<br>\n<strong>Output</strong>: 3<br>\n<strong>Explanation</strong>: <em>n = 3</em>, since size of the array is 3. 3 is missing from the array.</p>\n<h2 id=\"solution-1-sort\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#solution-1-sort\" aria-label=\"solution 1 sort permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Solution 1: Sort</h2>\n<h3 id=\"intuition\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#intuition\" aria-label=\"intuition permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Intuition</h3>\n<p>Sorting the array will result in <em>0, 1, 2, 3, …, n</em> this order with one number missing.\nIn other words, we can say, <em>nums[i]</em> will be equal to <em>i</em> (index). If it is not equal, we\ncan say that the current number is missing. Even after looping over the entire\narray, if we don’t find the missing number, the missing number will be <em>nums.size()</em>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"implementation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#implementation\" aria-label=\"implementation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Implementation</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><pre class=\"language-cpp\"><code class=\"language-cpp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> <span class=\"token function\">missingNumber</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vector<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">sort</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">begin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">end</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token operator\">++</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">!=</span> i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> i<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"complexity-analysis\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#complexity-analysis\" aria-label=\"complexity analysis permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Complexity Analysis</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Time Complexity</strong>: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>o</mi><msub><mi>g</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(nlog_2n)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">o</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.03588em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> for sorting and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(n)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> for the loop. Thus, overall\ntime complexity <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>o</mi><msub><mi>g</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(nlog_2n)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">o</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.03588em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>.</li>\n<li><strong>Space Complexity</strong>: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, as we are using constant space.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"solution-2-hash-table\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#solution-2-hash-table\" aria-label=\"solution 2 hash table permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Solution 2: Hash Table</h2>\n<h3 id=\"intuition-1\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#intuition-1\" aria-label=\"intuition 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Intuition</h3>\n<p>We can simply check if all the numbers from <em>0</em> to <em>n</em> exists in the array. We can\nefficiently do this checking using a hash table. Since hash table has a lookup\ntime complexity of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, the overall time complexity never exceeds <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(n)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"implementation-1\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#implementation-1\" aria-label=\"implementation 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Implementation</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><pre class=\"language-cpp\"><code class=\"language-cpp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> <span class=\"token function\">missingNumber</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vector<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    unordered_set <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token function\">numSet</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">begin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">end</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> expectedNums <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;=</span> expectedNums<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token operator\">++</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>numSet<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">find</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">==</span> numSet<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">end</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> i<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">__builtin_unreachable</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// unreachable code</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// replace by __assume(false) if you are using Microsoft Visual Studio C++</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"complexity-analysis-1\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#complexity-analysis-1\" aria-label=\"complexity analysis 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Complexity Analysis</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Time Complexity</strong>: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(n)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>.</li>\n<li><strong>Space Complexity</strong>: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(n)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> for storing the elements in the hash table.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"solution-3-xor\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#solution-3-xor\" aria-label=\"solution 3 xor permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Solution 3: XOR</h2>\n<h3 id=\"intuition-2\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#intuition-2\" aria-label=\"intuition 2 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Intuition</h3>\n<p>XOR is its own inverse. We can use this self-inverse property of XOR operations\nto find the missing number.</p>\n<p>Let’s assume a number k is missing. We can show that, all the numbers will get cancelled except\nk.</p>\n<p>(0 ^ 1 ^ 2 ^ … ^ n) ^ (nums[0] ^ nums[1] ^ … ^ nums[n - 1])<br>\n= (0 ^ 0) ^ (1 ^ 1) ^ (2 ^ 2) ^ … ^ k ^ … ^ (n ^ n) [XOR operations are\nassociative, <em>k</em> will not have a corresponding element from <em>nums</em>]<br>\n= 0 ^ 0 ^ 0 ^ … ^ k ^ … ^ 0<br>\n= k</p>\n<h3 id=\"implementation-2\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#implementation-2\" aria-label=\"implementation 2 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Implementation</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><pre class=\"language-cpp\"><code class=\"language-cpp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> <span class=\"token function\">missingNumber</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vector<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> missingNum <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token operator\">++</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        missingNum <span class=\"token operator\">^=</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">^</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> missingNum<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"complexity-analysis-2\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#complexity-analysis-2\" aria-label=\"complexity analysis 2 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Complexity Analysis</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Time Complexity</strong>: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(n)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, the <em>for</em> loop runs for <em>n</em> times.</li>\n<li><strong>Space Complexity</strong>: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, we are using constant space.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"solution-4-sum-of-n-natural-numbers\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#solution-4-sum-of-n-natural-numbers\" aria-label=\"solution 4 sum of n natural numbers permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Solution 4: Sum of n Natural Numbers</h2>\n<h3 id=\"intuition-3\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#intuition-3\" aria-label=\"intuition 3 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Intuition</h3>\n<p>We can obtain the missing number by summing all number from 0 to n and then subtract\nsum of array elements from it. The formula <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>∗</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n * (n + 1) / 2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.46528em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span></span></span></span> can be used to calculate\n<em>0 + 1 + 2 + … + n</em>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"implementation-3\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#implementation-3\" aria-label=\"implementation 3 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Implementation</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><pre class=\"language-cpp\"><code class=\"language-cpp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> <span class=\"token function\">missingNumber</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vector<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> n <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> withoutMissingSum <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> n <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>n <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// calculate sum of all the elements of nums</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> withMissingSum <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">accumulate</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">begin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">end</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> withoutMissingSum <span class=\"token operator\">-</span> withMissingSum<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"complexity-analysis-3\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#complexity-analysis-3\" aria-label=\"complexity analysis 3 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Complexity Analysis</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Time Complexity</strong>: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(n)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>.</li>\n<li><strong>Space Complexity</strong>: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"solution-5-calculating-offset\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#solution-5-calculating-offset\" aria-label=\"solution 5 calculating offset permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Solution 5: Calculating Offset</h2>\n<h3 id=\"intuition-4\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#intuition-4\" aria-label=\"intuition 4 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Intuition</h3>\n<p>One issue of the above approach is that for big <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span></span></span></span>, the sum can overflow. Thus,\ninstead of summing we can calculate the offset while looping over the array and\nat the end subtract <em>offset</em> from <em>nums.size()</em>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"implementation-4\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#implementation-4\" aria-label=\"implementation 4 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Implementation</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><pre class=\"language-cpp\"><code class=\"language-cpp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> <span class=\"token function\">missingNumber</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vector<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> offset <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token operator\">++</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        offset <span class=\"token operator\">+=</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">-</span> i<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> nums<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">-</span> offset<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"complexity-analysis-4\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#complexity-analysis-4\" aria-label=\"complexity analysis 4 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Complexity Analysis</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Time Complexity</strong>: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(n)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>.</li>\n<li><strong>Space Complexity</strong>: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O(1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, we are using constant space.</li>\n</ul>","fields":{"slug":"/dsa/missing-number/","tagSlugs":["/tag/cpp/","/tag/difficulty-easy/","/tag/sort/","/tag/bit-manipulation/","/tag/math/","/tag/hash-table/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-12-26","description":"Given an array containing n distinct integers in the range [0, n], one number is missing from the array. Find the missing number.","tags":["cpp","Difficulty: Easy","Sort","Bit Manipulation","Math","Hash Table"],"title":"Find One Missing Number in a Range","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/dsa/missing-number/"}}}